Overview of Changes in the Current Amendment:

Description of Change

{Brief Rationale for Change}

Section # and Name

Update screening language:

Edit the rescreening language

To allow for the repeat of screening assessments within the screening window or to allow a subject to rescreen once for the study. Due to the nature of the participant population and the study design, subject safety and data integrity will not be impacted

5.4.1 Rescreening

Clarify inclusion and exclusion criteria:

Move exclusion criterion 18 to the inclusion criteria and clarify the CYP450 enzymes that are excluded for exclusion criterion 19.

Previous exclusion 18 should be answered affirmatively in order for the subject to be eligible for participation; as a result, this exclusion should be listed as an inclusion. Exclusion 19 excluded all inducers of metabolism; however, after consideration, it is only necessary to exclude inducers of CYP3A4.

5.2 Exclusion Criteria

Clarify procedure for continuous end tidal CO2:

Add clarification that subjects may remove cannula to dose or eat

The timepoints overlap for the collection of end tidal CO2 and it would not be possible for the subject to dose or eat with the cannula in place.

7.2.8 Continuous and Spot End Tidal Carbon Dioxide, Table 5, Established Limits for End Tidal Carbon Dioxide

Lower the respiratory rate alarm for continuous end tidal CO2 alarms:

The alarm for respiratory rate low was 10 bpm and is now 6 bpm.

Generally, respiratory rates between 6 and 10 are not clinically relevant. A low respiratory rate alarm of 6 will allow a more accurate clinical determination of a true signal.

7.2.8 Continuous and Spot End Tidal Carbon Dioxide, Table 5, Established Limits

Edit Spot CO2 respiratory rate values:

The spot values are lowered to start at > 24, and continue with increments of 4 bpm: >28, >32, and >36.

This change is made to align with the protocol, Table 7, alarm values.

Key aspects of the trial design are summarised below.

Intervention Model:

Open Label

Population Type:

Without disease

Control Type:

Placebo controlled

Population Diagnosis or Condition:

Opiod use

Control Description:

Placebo

Population Age:

Minimum: 18 years

Maximum: 60 years

Intervention Assignment Method:

Randomization

Site Distribution and Geographic Scope:

Single site

Number of Arms: 3

Trial Blind Schema: Double-blind

Blinded roles: The following roles indicated will not be made aware of the treatment group assignment during the trial: participant, investigator

Number of Participants:

Approximately 24 male and female participants to complete at least 18 participants. An attempt will be made to enroll 1 female participant for every 3 male participants.

Duration

The anticipated duration of the study for each participant, including screening and follow-up, is approximately 53 days.

Committees:

Independent Committees: Not applicable.
